@startuml pdf-cache-page-restore
title PDF Browser Cache + Instant Page Restore

participant "Participant JS" as JS
participant "PdfCache\n(IndexedDB)" as IDB
participant "Railway / Daemon" as Server
participant "Daemon WS" as WS

== Happy path — cached, no update ==

JS -> JS: loadPdf(url, slug, dAt, targetPage)
JS -> JS: show #pdf-loading-overlay
JS -> IDB: get(slug, dAt)
IDB --> JS: HIT — return buffer
note right: no network request
JS -> JS: pdfjsLib.getDocument({data: buffer})
JS -> JS: renderAllPages()
JS -> JS: _scrollSlidesToPage(targetPage)
note right: synchronous, no setTimeout
JS -> JS: hide #pdf-loading-overlay
note right: user sees correct page instantly

== Cache miss — first load or after invalidation ==

JS -> IDB: get(slug, dAt)
IDB --> JS: MISS — null (missing or stale dAt)
JS -> Server: fetch(url)
Server --> JS: 200 + PDF bytes
JS -> IDB: put(slug, dAt, buffer)
note right: saved for next load
JS -> JS: render + scroll + reveal (as above)

== PPTX updated — online participant (WS path) ==

WS -> JS: DecksUpdatedMsg (new dAt for slug)
JS -> IDB: invalidate(slug)
IDB --> JS: deleted
note right: proactive eviction
JS -> JS: loadPdf() triggered by follow/reload
JS -> IDB: get(slug, newDAt)
IDB --> JS: MISS
JS -> Server: fetch(url)
Server --> JS: new PDF bytes
note right: fresh PDF delivered

== PPTX updated — reconnecting participant (missed WS) ==

JS -> Server: GET /api/participant/state
Server --> JS: state with new dAt for slug
note right: _slidesCacheStatus refreshed
JS -> JS: loadPdf(url, slug, newDAt, targetPage)
JS -> IDB: get(slug, newDAt)
IDB --> JS: MISS — dAt mismatch with stored entry
note right: implicit invalidation — no extra code needed
JS -> Server: fetch(url)
Server --> JS: new PDF bytes
note right: fresh PDF delivered

@enduml
